Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Friday and welcome back to our 73rd Weekly Dose of Optimism. This wil=
l be out final post of the year here at Not Boring, and what a year it=E2=
=80=99s been!
AI has gone mainstream. Drug discovery and development seem to have hit esc=
ape velocity. Nuclear has the most momentum it=E2=80=99s had in over half a=
 century. The robots are coming. The economy didn=E2=80=99t melt down. And =
you could probably start a legitimate space startup in your college dorm ro=
om (h/t Jeff Bezos).=20
2023 was obviously not without its challenges =E2=80=94 there are wars ragi=
ng in Europe and the Middle East as we speak. We=E2=80=99re not ignoring al=
l of that, but we are optimistic about the future. The kind of optimism we=
=E2=80=99re talking about is =E2=80=9Cthe very optimistic belief that thing=
s will inevitably go wrong, but that each new challenge is an opportunity f=
or further progress.=E2=80=9D And on that front, we=E2=80=99ve had a great =
year.=20
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
